cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.SI

The paper deals with the application of deep learning models for shape completion of mandible bones in virtual planning of jaw reconstructive surgery. This involves the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and machine learning algorithms (cs.LG) for optimization and training of the models. The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic models (cs.MM) and the evaluation of the model's ability to generate anatomically relevant variations (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of 3D imaging and modeling techniques (cs.GR) for the reconstruction of the missing segments of the bone.
